<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>uv on Bossagyu Blog</title><link>https://bossagyu.com/en/tags/uv/</link><description>Recent content in uv on Bossagyu Blog</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-US</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 01 Jan 2025 14:39:53 +0900</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://bossagyu.com/en/tags/uv/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Setting Up a Python Development Environment on Mac with UV</title><link>https://bossagyu.com/en/blog/032-python-uv/</link><pubDate>Wed, 01 Jan 2025 14:39:53 +0900</pubDate><guid>https://bossagyu.com/en/blog/032-python-uv/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="overview">Overview&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>This article introduces how to set up a Python development environment on Mac using UV.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="what-is-uv">What is UV?&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>UV is a package management tool announced in mid-2024.&lt;br>
It is written in Rust and is characterized by faster performance compared to other package managers.&lt;/p>
